The paper deals with lower bounds for approximating the max cut value in the streaming model of computation, which involves processing data in a sequential manner with limited memory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the sense that it considers the amount of space required to obtain certain approximations, and machine learning (cs.LG) in the sense that it deals with the problem of learning a property of a graph (bipartiteness). Finally, the paper involves graph theory (cs.DM) in the sense that it considers the max cut problem and the size of a maximum matching.
